11. b3 { White aims to fianchetto their bishop on b2. } 11... Nh4
{ Aiming to get a position where we'd have the pair of bishops vs a knight + bishop. }
12. Nd4 Bd7 { Preparing to bring our rook to d8. } 13. Bb2 Rd8 14. Ne4 f6
{ We are now prepared to open up the position for our bishops. } 15. e6
{ White correctly tries to keep matters 'closed'. } 15... Bc8 16. g3
{ Would be great, if not for our intermediate move! } 16... f5
{ A nice resource which doesn't allow White to strengthen their e6-pawn by means of f4, f5. }
17. gxh4 fxe4 18. Nf5 Bf6
{ Black is somewhat better, as the e6-pawn will eventually fall. } *

