15... b6 { We can fianchetto our bishop in response as well! } 16. c4 Bb7
{ We are ready to play c5, opening the long light diagonal for our bishop to enjoy, making the position pleasant for us.   17.c5  will be met by  17...Ba6  , taking advantage of the newly opened f1-a6 diagonal, attacking White’s knight on e2.  18.N2c3  will be answered with  18...Rd8  , with better chances for Black, since the pawn on c5 can only improve our structure by removing our doubled pawns. Avoiding it is difficult, since White's knight on e4 is blocked protecting c5. }
