19. Be3 Kd7
{ An aesthetically pleasing maneuver. The king will be better placed on the queenside. }
20. Rad1+ Kc8 21. Rxd8+ Bxd8
{ The position is balanced, as White will struggle to find ways of making progress. We will continue with our usual space grab on the queenside with c5 and a5. }
