{ Black is somewhat better thanks to their pair of bishops and multiple targets in White's position.   The pawn on f5 is weak and so is the g3 one. The knight on c3 has limited prospects and we can push it even further by means of b5, b4, after which our light-squared bishop can occupy the a8-h1 diagonal. }
