11. Nxh4
{ 11.Rd1+  Ke8  transposes to @@StartFEN@@r1bk1b1r/ppp2ppp/2p5/4Pn2/8/5N2/PPP2PPP/RNB2RK1 w - - 0 9@@EndFEN@@  9.Rd1  Ke8  10.Nc3  Be7  11.h3  Nh4  line. }
11... Bxh4 12. Be3 { A natural way of continuing the development. } 12... h5
{ Making g4 hard to achieve. } 13. Rad1+
