11. Bxc6 Be6
{ We can throw in this move or take on c6 immediately- both will lead to the same position. }
12. Qb5 bxc6 13. Qxc6 Bg4
{ Simply the simplest, bothering White's knight on f3, which they can't really support, basically forcing it to retreat. }
14. Nd2 Rfd8
{ The rook belongs to an open file. We need to improve the position of every piece in order to claim good compensation for the sacrificed pawn. }
15. Nc4 Qg6
{ Creating the threat of  16.--  Bh3  , while keeping an eye on the e4-pawn. Another idea to remember is 'hunting down' White's queen by means of Bd7. Black has enough compensation to keep the position balanced. }
