12. Rxd1 Bb6
{ The bishop must stay on the a7-g1 diagonal in order to keep an eye on the f2-pawn, thus preventing it from moving to f3, from where it would protect its brother on e4. }
13. Nc4 Nxe4 { Getting back the sacrificed pawn. } 14. Nxb6 cxb6 15. f3 Nc5
{ We are not afraid of doubling our c-pawns, as White won't have any ways of exploiting it. The position is equal. }
