{ The time has come to open up White's king! } 18. gxh3 Qe6
{ 19.--  Qxh3  followed by a mate on g2 is a threat hard to deal with. } 19.
Qd2 Rhf8
{ The rook protects the knight and gets ready to go to f6, from where it may later have the possibility to slide to g6. }
20. Qe3 Rf6
{ There was no need to rush taking the h3-pawn, as White doesn't have a good way of protecting it anyway.  20...Qxh3  would actually be a mistake in view of  21.Ne1    The text move will give us additional Rg6 ideas, which keep the position balanced, though it's White who has to be very precise to avoid getting mated. }
