{ The bishop is well-placed on e6 as it controls the c4-square and won't get shut out after our typical Nd7, f6 maneuver. }
7. Be3
{ Aiming to trade the bishops in a move order where we can’t follow it up with 8...Bg4. }
7... Bxe3
{ Still the best choice for us, as our bishop doesn’t have any good prospects if it has to leave c5. }
8. fxe3 Nd7
{ With a slight edge for Black thanks to our potential play on the kingside. We’ll continue by bringing our queen to e7, preparing a long castle. We can then follow up with f7-f6- a multifunctional move that prepares both a pawn storm on the kingside by means of g5 and creates the f7-square for our bishop to retreat, shall we need the e6-square for our knight. }
