{ The best square for the knight. At the same time, White doesn't hurry with castling, waiting to see our setup first. It is the best scoring move for White and the most popular one. }
6... Be6 { Stopping White from jumping to c4. } 7. Nb3 Bb6
{ It is important to cover the a5-square, hence our bishop is retreating to b6 rather than to d6 - as after  7...Bd6  8.Na5  , White would have a small edge. }
8. O-O { Allows our usual plan of preparing a pawn storm on the kingside. }
8... Qe7
{ The e5-pawn is untouchable, as White would drop a piece after  9.Nxe5  Bxb3  . }
9. Qe1
{ White's queen heads towards c3, from where it will put pressure on our e5-pawn. }
9... Nd7
{ Our favourite maneuver, preparing f6 and protecting the e5-pawn.  10.Na5  will be met by  10...Qc5  , with a double attack on a5 and c2. }
10. Qc3 f6
{ The position is balanced, as we'll continue with the long castle and then the pawn roll on the kingside. }
