{ Why not take this square away from White's knight for good, while also planning to force it back by means of a4? }
10. Nbd2 Bxe3 11. fxe3 a4
{ Taking space on the queenside was part of our plan, and we can now continue with the other part of it - bring the knight to  d7 and push f6 to protect our e5-pawn. Then we could castle short and continue grabbing space on the queenside by pushing  c5 and b5. The position is balanced. }
