{ 10.Bxf6  Qxf6  would lead to Black's advantage thanks to the pair of bishops. }
10. Bh4 g5 11. dxe5 Nxe4 12. Bd3 gxh4 13. Bxe4 Re8 14. Re1 d6
{ Despite our opened king, we enjoy an advantage thanks to the pair of bishops and White is not being able to create threats against our king.   15.exd6  will be met by the cool  15...Re6!  , taking advantage of White’s not being able to take on c7, as they would lose the bishop on e4 after Black will trade queens. This means that we’ll be able to recapture on d6 with the rook, with a nice edge thanks to our piece activity. }
