{ The most popular move. White makes the position resemble an Italian game, or Giuoco Piano, where their main idea is to play d4, getting control in the centre. }
7... Bb6
{ The best square for our bishop, as on c5 it would be exposed to b4 and d4 pushes. Although White has several ways to continue their development, none of them grant any advantage. }
8. Bg5
{ It's not a good idea to tempt us into playing h6, g5, as we will happily do so, taking advantage of our king not having castled yet. }
8... h6 9. Bh4
{ Freely giving up the pair of bishops didn't make sense, so White retreats. }
9... c6 10. Ba4 g5 11. Bg3
{ Why would White's bishop be better on g3 than on c1? This question doesn't have an answer. }
11... d6
{ Protecting the e5-pawn and planning on continuing the pawn storm on the kingside with h5-h4, where White's bishop will start missing the time when it was on c1. }
