O-O
{ Is likely to transpose to the @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pppp1ppp/2n2n2/1B2p3/4P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 4 4@@EndFEN@@  4.O-O  Nxe4  5.Re1  line, but with suboptimal moves already chosen by White.  In the mentioned line White still has the light-squared bishop and usually prefers to keep it on the board, whereas here, that option is gone. }
