15. fxe5 Be6 16. dxe4
{ It looks like White has won a pawn, but we have a nice and somewhat unusual way to get it back. }
16... Rg8
{ A tempo move, forcing white queen to f4 if they want to keep their extra pawn. }
17. Qf4 Rg5
{ A very cool, horizontal pin against White's bishop on b5. The e5-pawn can't move, meaning that we'll get it back as soon as we can by means of dxe5.   The position is somewhat better for us thanks to the control over the g-file and White's doubled c-pawns which can become a target after a potential Qe7-c5 maneuver. }
