13. fxe5 { An intermediate move, attacking our knight on f6. } 13... hxg5 14.
exf6 gxf6
{ Black is actually better thanks to the potential play in the centre after the incoming Qe7, Bd7, and Rae8, followed by a break in the centre by means of either f5 or c6, d5. Our king will feel safe on g7. }
