{ The best scoring move. The idea is to protect the e4-pawn without committing the pawn to d3, thus keeping the possibility of playing c3, d4 in one go. }
4... Bc5
{ The best square for our bishop as it fights against potential d4 ideas. } 5.
O-O { Bringing the king to safety first. } 5... O-O 6. d3
{ Doesn't run well with the concept behind Qe2, as White gives up the possibility of playing d4 in one go.   After  6.c3  Re8  , the position transposes to @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/2n2n2/1Bb1p3/4P3/5N2/PPPPQPPP/RNB1K2R w KQkq - 6 5@@EndFEN@@  5.c3  . }
