10... d6 { Stabilizing the e5-pawn while opening our light-squared bishop. }
11. Bc4 O-O 12. Ra3
{ A typical rook lift, hoping to bring the rook to business as fast as possible. }
12... Kh8
{ Prophylaxis- the x-ray over the a2-g8 diagonal was unpleasant. White is yet to prove their desired compensation for the sacrificed pawn, while we can simply continue our development by means of Bg4, then Qd7. }
