{ Conclusions:  1. Always think of the piece that can be improved and if the opponent has no immediate threats- go for it!  2. Once seizing the initiative- use the time wisely and continue creating threats!  3. A knight on the rim is dim- consider carefully before placing your knight on the edge of the board.  4. If it looks like the move you wanted to make is impossible, double-check it, perhaps there's a way to make it work- see @@StartFEN@@2r5/3n1ppk/5r1p/Nq2p3/pP1nP2P/R5P1/1R1N1PK1/3Q4 b - - 8 43@@EndFEN@@  43...Rc2!! }
