{ Conclusions:  1. @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/ppp1nppp/3p1n2/1B2p1B1/4P2N/2PP4/P1P2PPP/R2Q1RK1 b - - 3 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Ne8  is a move to be considered as an alternative to  9...Ng6  . It takes a little bit more risks, but in the same time- it keeps more pieces on the board, thus more possibilities for the opponent to go wrong.  2. Sacrificing a pawn in order to get the initiative is an important technique that can often change the fate of a game.  3. Take care for your pieces to be on the best possible squares and avoid those where they might feel cramped.  4. Stay tactically alert until the very end you can never know when your opponent may allow you a chance to get back in the game @@StartBracket@@see @@StartFEN@@3r2k1/1pp2p2/6pR/2nP2N1/2r5/8/6PP/4R1K1 w - - 0 32@@EndFEN@@  32.Rh8+  @@EndBracket@@  . }
